This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with interpretability in machine learning and proposes a training methodology for robust attribution. The paper also discusses the application of the proposed model in weakly supervised object localization and segmentation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of soft-margin triplet loss, which is a common technique in deep learning and falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the issue of safe deployment of machine learning systems, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for achieving state-of-the-art results, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
